[5] Chile
Date: Fri 17 Jun 2022
Source: La Tercera [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, abridged, edited]
https://www.latercera.com/nacional/noticia/minsal-confirma-el-primer-caso-de-viruela-del-mono-en-chile/XJ56P4Y7FND7BADAAICWBC6FDQ/


This afternoon [17 Jun 2022], the Ministry of Health (MINSAL) reported that the Institute of Public Health (ISP) confirmed Chile's 1st PCR test-positive monkeypox case.

According to the information provided in a statement MINSAL transmitted, the infected individual is a young adult from the Metropolitan Region with a history of travel to Europe and who presented symptoms of sudden exanthema (spots on the skin), vesiculated lesions, crusted skin accompanied by necrosis and swollen lymph nodes.

The Regional Health Authority, as they pointed out, applied the surveillance protocol established by the Ministry of Health, and the patient is in good health and without complications.

The ministry recommended that people consult a doctor if they have traveled abroad, have had close skin-to-skin contact, including sexual intercourse, and have sudden onset of unexplained skin lesions with one or more symptoms such as fever, swollen glands, muscle or back pain, and necrosis.

[Byline: Daniela Silva]

