[8] Romania
Date: Mon 13 Jun 2022 20:04 IST
Source: Devdiscourse [edited]
https://www.devdiscourse.com/article/health/2071440-romania-detects-its-first-case-of-monkeypox-health-ministry


Romania confirmed its 1st case of monkeypox -- a disease usually found in west and central Africa -- in a 26-year-old male from the capital Bucharest, the health ministry said on Monday [13 Jun 2022]. The patient, whose partner travelled recently in several European countries with numerous confirmed cases, is in a good condition and is being treated in isolation, the ministry said.

